----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Here are the current compiler and all the required tools as tar.gz version
for non Sparemint installations.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Attention: These archives are converted from the rpm versions
           and not tested.
           
           In general, it's recommended to install Sparemint instead.
           
           If you have problems or questions please ask first on the
           MiNT mailing list <mint@fishpool.com>.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

file description:
-----------------

binutils-2.9.1-6.m68kmint.tar.gz
- GNU binary utils
- contain as, ld, ar and all other tools + the complete documentation

cflib-11m-3.m68kmint.tar.gz
- Christian Felsch's cflib

gcc-2.95.2-4.m68kmint.tar.gz
- GNU Compiler Collection
- contain the C, C++ and Object-C compiler, complete documentation

gemlib-38-4.m68kmint.tar.gz
- the GEMLIB with the all GEM/VDI bindings and all new enhancements

mint-util-0.2.1-1.m68kmint.tar.gz
- contain at the moment only crlf to strip down carrige returns

mintbin-0.3-3.m68kmint.tar.gz
- additional tools for the m68k-atari-mint a.out format
- tools for stacksize correction, program flags setting, libarary converter

mintlib-0.55-2.m68kmint.tar.gz
- the complete MiNTLib
- including the timezone database, tzinit tool, the header files
  and all the required libs

mintnet-1.04-4.m68kmint.tar.gz
- include the sockets and all drivers for the supported hardware

pml-2.03-3.m68kmint.tar.gz
- math library
- required for C++


----------------------------------------------------------------------------

installation informations:
--------------------------

(only some notes, not complete)

- the GCC set require an filesystem with Unix mode bits!

  unpack the archives best on an ext2 filesystem and link
  usr to /usr (sln directive in MiNT.CNF)

- verify that /usr/bin is in your $PATH of your shell

- test the GCC installation with 'gcc -v'
  if all things are installed correctly you must get the following message:
  
  Reading specs from /usr/lib/gcc-lib/m68k-atari-mint/2.95.2/specs
  gcc version 2.95.2 19991024 (release)
  
  if not something is wrong and you must first solve the problem
  before you can proceed
  
- second test: compile a simple hello world program:
  
  create the following hello.c file:
  --- cut ---
  #include <stdlib.h>
  
  int
  main(void) {
        printf ("Hello world!\n");
        return 0;
  }
  -- paste ---
  
  and then compile it:
  
  bash> gcc -o hello hello.c
  bash> ./hello
  Hello world!
  bash> 
  
  If you see this all things work ok. Congratulations.
  
- if you try to compile GNU packages you need mostly additional Unix tools:
  make, sed, gawk, perl, sh-utils, fileutils and so on

- the new GCC doesn't work correctly with ATARI linefeed textfiles;
  you must strip the ATARI linefeeds with the crlfs tool first if you
  have such source files

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Have fun and please read the documentation!

If somebody have written a better installation text I'm happy to put it here.


Frank Naumann
